obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (44326)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00027_187806_1523270020940&sectionId=44326&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00027_187806_1523270020940
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `This Act may be called the Indian Treasure-trove Act, 1878.`
  line
  line `Extent.--It extends to the whole of India except ^1[the territories which, immediately before the 1st`
  line `November, 1956, were comprised in Part B States].`
  line
  line `^2* * * * *`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line Maharashtra
  line
  line `In the principal Act,--In section 1,--`
  line
  line `(i) to the second paragraph the following proviso shall be added, namely:--`
  line
  line `"Provided that on the commencement of the Indian Treasure-trove (Extension to Hyderabad and`
  line `Saurashtra area of Bombay State) Act, 1957 (Bom. XXXIII of 1958), this Act shall also extend to and`
  line `be in force in, the Hyderabad and Saurashtra area of the State of Bombay."`
  line
  line `(ii) against the proviso so inserted the marginal note "commencement in certain areas" shall be`
  line inserted;
  line
  line `[Vide Bombay Act XXXIII of 1958, s. 3]`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by the Adaptation of Laws (No. 2) Order, 1956, for "Part B States".`
  line
  line `2. The words "And it shall come into force at once." rep. by Act 10 of 1914, s. 3 and the Second Schedule.`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (44327)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title [Repealed.].
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00027_187806_1523270020940&sectionId=44327&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00027_187806_1523270020940
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `[Repeal of enactments.] Rep. by the Repealing and Amending Act, 1891 (12 of 1891), s. 2 and the`
  line `First Schedule.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (44328)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title Interpretation-clause.
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00027_187806_1523270020940&sectionId=44328&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00027_187806_1523270020940
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `In this Act--`
  line
  line `Treasure.-- "treasure" means anything of any value hidden in the soil, or in anything affixed`
  line thereto;
  line
  line `Collector.-- "Collector" means (1) any Revenue Officer in independent charge of a`
  line `district, and (2) any officer appointed by the State Government to perform the functions`
  line `of a Collector under this Act.`
  line
  line `Owner.--"OWNER" means when any person is entitled, under any reservation in an instrument of`
  line `transfer of any land or thing affixed thereto, to treasure in such land or thing, he shall, for the`
  line `purposes of this Act, be deemed to be the owner of such land or thing.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (44329)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Notice by finder of treasure.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00027_187806_1523270020940&sectionId=44329&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00027_187806_1523270020940
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `Whenever any treasure exceeding in amount or value ten rupees is`
  line `found, the finder shall, as soon as practicable, give to the Collector notice in writing--`
  line
  line `(a) of the nature and amount or approximate value of such treasure;`
  line
  line `(b) of the place in which it was found;`
  line
  line `(c) of the date of the finding;`
  line
  line `and either deposit the treasure in the nearest Government treasury, or give the Collector such`
  line `security as the Collector thinks fit, to produce the treasure at such time and place as he may`
  line `from time to time require.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (44330)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Notification requiring claimants to appear.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00027_187806_1523270020940&sectionId=44330&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00027_187806_1523270020940
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `On receiving a notice under section 4, the`
  line `Collector shall, after making such enquiry (if any) as he thinks fit, take the following steps`
  line `(namely):--`
  line
  line `(a) he shall publish a notification in such manner as the State Government from time to`
  line `time prescribes in this behalf, to the effect that, on a certain date (mentioning it) certain`
  line `treasure (mentioning its nature, amount and approximate value) was found in a certain place`
  line `(mentioning it); and requiring all persons claiming the treasure, or any part thereof, to appear`
  line `personally or by agent before the Collector on a day and at a place therein mentioned, such`
  line `day not being earlier than four months, or later than six months, after the date of the`
  line `publication of such notification;`
  line `(b) when the place in which the treasure appears to the Collector to have been found was at`
  line `the date of the finding in the possession of some person other than the finder, the Collector`
  line `shall also serve on such person a special notice in writing to the same effect.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (44331)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Forfeiture of right on failure to appear.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00027_187806_1523270020940&sectionId=44331&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00027_187806_1523270020940
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `Any person having any right to such treasure`
  line `or any part thereof, as owner of the place in which it was found or otherwise, and not appearing`
  line `as required by the notification issued under section 5, shall forfeit such right.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (44332)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Matters to be enquired into and determined by the Collector.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00027_187806_1523270020940&sectionId=44332&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00027_187806_1523270020940
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `On the day notified under`
  line `section 5, the Collector shall cause the treasure to be produced before him, and shall enquire as to`
  line `and determine--`
  line
  line `(a) the person by whom, the place in which, and the circumstances under which, such treasure`
  line `was found; and`
  line
  line `(b) as far as is possible the person by whom, and the circumstances under which, such treasure`
  line `was hidden.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (44333)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Time to be allowed for suit by person claiming the treasure.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00027_187806_1523270020940&sectionId=44333&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00027_187806_1523270020940
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `If, upon an enquiry made`
  line `under section 7, the Collector sees reason to believe that the treasure was hidden within one`
  line `hundred years before the date of the finding, by a person appearing as required by the said`
  line `notification and claiming such treasure, or by some other person under whom such person claims,`
  line `the Collector shall make an order adjourning the hearing of the case for such period as he deems`
  line `sufficient, to allow of a suit being instituted in the Civil Court by the claimant, to establish his`
  line right.
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (44334)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `When treasure may be declared ownerless.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes `1. For definition of Chief Controlling Revenue authority, see the General Clauses Act, 1897 (10 of 1897), s. 3(10).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00027_187806_1523270020940&sectionId=44334&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00027_187806_1523270020940
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `If upon such enquiry the Collector sees no reason`
  line `to believe that the treasure was so hidden; or`
  line
  line `if, where a period is fixed under section 8, no suit is instituted as aforesaid within such period to the`
  line `knowledge of the Collector; or`
  line
  line `if such suit is instituted within such period, and the plaintiff's claim is finally rejected;`
  line
  line `the Collector may declare the treasure to be ownerless.`
  line
  line `Appeal against such declaration.--Any person aggrieved by a declaration made under this`
  line `section may appeal against the same within two months from the date thereof to the Chief`
  line `Controlling Revenue authority.^1`
  line
  line `Subject to such appeal, every such declaration shall be final and conclusive.`
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (44335)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Proceedings subsequent to declaration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00027_187806_1523270020940&sectionId=44335&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00027_187806_1523270020940
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `When a declaration has been made in respect`
  line `of any treasure under section 9, such treasure shall, in accordance with the provisions hereinafter`
  line `contained, either be delivered to the finder thereof, or be divided between him and the owner of`
  line `the place in which it has been found in manner hereinafter provided.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (44336)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `When no other person claims as owner of place, treasure to be given to finder.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00027_187806_1523270020940&sectionId=44336&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00027_187806_1523270020940
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line When
  line `a declaration has been made in respect of any treasure as aforesaid, and no person other than the`
  line `finder of such treasure has appeared as required by the notification published under section 5 and`
  line `claimed a share of the treasure as owner of the place in which it has been found, the Collector shall`
  line `deliver such treasure to the finder thereof.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (44348)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `When only one such person claims and his claim is not disputed,treasure to be divided,and shares to be delivered to parties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00027_187806_1523270020940&sectionId=44348&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00027_187806_1523270020940
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `When a declaration has been made as aforesaid in respect of`
  line `any treasure, and only one person other than the finder of such treasure has so appeared and claimed,`
  line `and the claim of such person is not disputed by the finder, the Collector shall proceed to divide the`
  line `treasure between the finder and the person so claiming according to the following rule (namely):--`
  line
  line `If the finder and the person so claiming have not entered into any agreement then in force`
  line `as to the disposal of the treasure, three-fourths of the treasure shall be allotted to such finder`
  line `and the residue to such person. If such finder and such person have entered into any such`
  line `agreement, the treasure shall be disposed of in accordance therewith:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Collector may in any case, if he thinks fit, instead of dividing any treasure as`
  line `directed by this section,--`
  line
  line `(a) allot to either party the whole or more than his share of such treasure, on such party`
  line `paying to the Collector for the other party such sum of money as the Collector may fix a s the`
  line `equivalent of the share of such other party, or of the excess so allotted, as the case may be; or`
  line
  line `(b) sell such treasure or any portion thereof by public auction and divide the sale-proceeds`
  line `between the parties according to the rule hereinbefore prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided also, that when the Collector has by his declaration under section 9 rejected any`
  line `claim made under this Act by any person other than the said finder or person claiming as owner`
  line `of the place in which the treasure was found, such division shall not be made until after the`
  line `expiration of two months without an appeal having been presented under section 9 by the person`
  line `whose claim has been so rejected, or, when an appeal has been so presented, after such appeal`
  line `has been dismissed.`
  line
  line `When the Collector has made a division under this section, he shall deliver to the parties the`
  line `portions of such treasure, or the money in lieu thereof, to which they are respectively entitled`
  line `under such division.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (44338)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `In case of dispute as to ownership of place, proceedings to be stayed.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00027_187806_1523270020940&sectionId=44338&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00027_187806_1523270020940
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `When a`
  line `declaration has been made as aforesaid in respect of any treasure, and two or more persons have`
  line `appeared as aforesaid and each of them claimed as owner of the place where such treasure was found,`
  line `or the right of any person who has so appeared and claimed is disputed by the finder of such treasure,`
  line `the Collector shall retain such treasure and shall make an order staying his proceedings with a view`
  line `to the matter being enquired into and determined by a Civil Court.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (44339)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Settlement of such dispute.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00027_187806_1523270020940&sectionId=44339&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00027_187806_1523270020940
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `Any person who has so appeared and claimed may, within one`
  line `month from the date of such order, institute a suit in the Civil Court to obtain a decree declaring his right;`
  line `and in every such suit the finder of the treasure and all persons disputing such claim before the Collector`
  line `shall be made defendants.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (44340)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `And division thereupon.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00027_187806_1523270020940&sectionId=44340&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00027_187806_1523270020940
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `If any such suit is instituted and the plaintiff's claim is finally`
  line `established therein, the Collector shall, subject to the provisions of section 12, divide the treasure between`
  line `him and the finder.`
  line
  line `If no such suit is instituted as aforesaid, or if the claims of the plaintiffs in all such suits are finally`
  line `rejected, the Collector shall deliver the treasure to the finder.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (44341)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Power to acquire the treasure on behalf of Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00027_187806_1523270020940&sectionId=44341&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00027_187806_1523270020940
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `The Collector may, at any time after`
  line `making a declaration under section 9, and before delivering or dividing the treasure as hereinbefore`
  line `provided, declare by writing under his hand his intention to acquire on behalf of the Government the`
  line `treasure, or any specified portion thereof, by payment to the persons entitled thereto of a sum equal to the`
  line `value of the materials of such treasure or portion, together with one-fifth of such value, and may place`
  line `such sum in deposit in his treasury to the credit of such persons; and thereupon such treasure or portion`
  line `shall be deemed to be the property of Government, and the money so deposited shall be dealt with, as far`
  line `as is may be, as if it were such treasure or portion.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (44342)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Decision of Collector final, and no suit to lie against him for acts done bona fide.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00027_187806_1523270020940&sectionId=44342&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00027_187806_1523270020940
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line No
  line `decision passed or act done by the Collector under this Act shall be called in question by any Civil Court,`
  line `and no suit or other proceeding shall lie against him for anything done in good faith in exercise of the`
  line `powers hereby conferred.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (44343)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Collector to exercise powers of Civil Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes `1. See now the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00027_187806_1523270020940&sectionId=44343&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00027_187806_1523270020940
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `A Collector making any enquiry under this Act`
  line `may exercise any power conferred by the Code of Civil Procedure^1`
  line `(14 of 1882) on a Civil Court for the`
  line `trial of suits.`
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (44344)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00027_187806_1523270020940&sectionId=44344&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00027_187806_1523270020940
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `^1[The State Government may, from time to time, make rules consistent`
  line `with this Act, to regulate proceedings hereunder.`
  line `Such rules shall, on being published in the Official Gazette, have the force of law.]`
  line
  line `^2[(2) Every rule made by the State Government under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may`
  line `be after it is made, before the State Legislature.]`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 4 of 2005, s. 2 and the Schedule (w.e.f. 11-01-2005).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by ibid., s. 2 and the Schedule. (w.e.f. 11-01-2005).`
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (44345)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Penalty on finder failing to give notice, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00027_187806_1523270020940&sectionId=44345&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00027_187806_1523270020940
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `If the finder of any treasure fails to give the`
  line `notice, or does not either make the deposit or give the security, required by section 4, or alters or`
  line `attempts to alter such treasure so as to conceal its identity, the share of such treasur e, or the money`
  line `in lieu thereof to which he would otherwise be entitled, shall vest in Government,`
  line
  line `and he shall, on conviction before a Magistrate, be punished with imprisonment for a term which may`
  line `extend to one year, or with fine, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (44346)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Penalty on owner abetting offence under section 20.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00027_187806_1523270020940&sectionId=44346&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00027_187806_1523270020940
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `If the owner of the place in which any`
  line `treasure is found abets, within the meaning of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860), any offence under`
  line `section 20, the share of such treasure, or the money in lieu thereof to which he would otherwise be`
  line `entitled, shall vest in Government,`
  line
  line `and he shall, on conviction before a Magistrate, be punished with imprisonment which may extend to`
  line `six months, or with fine, or with both.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line Maharashtra
  line
  line `after section 21, the following section be inserted, namely:--`
  line
  line `"22. Repeal and savings.--The Hyderabad Treasure-Trove Act, 1322F (Hyd. III of 1322F ), and`
  line `the Indian Treasure-trove Act, 1878, as modified and applied by the State of Saurashtra (Application`
  line `of Central and Bombay Acts) Ordinance, 1948 (San. Ord. XXV of 1948), are hereby repealed:`
  line
  line `Provided that, notwithstanding such repeal, anything done or action taken (including any notice`
  line `or security given, any forfeiture, determination, declaration, delivery, division, acquisition or order`
  line `made, all rights, obligations and liabilities acquired, accrued or incurred, penalties imposed, and all`
  line `proceedings and appeals pending before the Collector, Chief Controlling Revenue Authority,`
  line `Talukdar, Subedar, Board of Revenue or other authority, and all powers conferred therefor) by or`
  line `under the provisions of any law so repealed shall be deemed to be done, taken given, made, acquired,`
  line `accrued, incurred, imposed, pending or conferred, under the provisions of this Act, as if this Act had`
  line `then been in force; and accordingly all such proceedings and appeals pending before any such`
  line `authority as aforesaid shall stand transferred, where necessary, to the corresponding authority under`
  line `this Act; and if no such authority exists or if there be a doubt as to the corresponding authority, to`
  line `such authority as the State Government may designate, and shall be continued and disposed of before`
  line `such authority in accordance with the provisions of this Act,"`
  line
  line `[Vide Bombay Act XXXIII of 1958, s. 3]`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
